replies.body:
So much yes in this thread. Riot's one of my favourites when it comes to character design, they always come up with such beautifully done champions. Everything from their lore to their overall aesthetic is always just 
{{sticker:sg-kiko}} 

Of all the champion's in the game though, {{champion:127}} takes the cake in terms of character design for me. She's THE champion that actually got me to look into the lore of league. Like League lore isn't bad by any means, but I could never quite get fully invested into it like I do with other games' lore. Lissandra's design as a whole just clicked with me in general and I just had to find out more about her. Her graceful but imposing demeanor and almost alien monolithic figure, that amazing voice work and probably the most satisfying and visceral skill animations and audio cues. Her background which was just awesome and badass, even the fact that she's one of the few purely black character in the game. Like she's not evil because of some tragic backstory, she just straight up wants to enslave the world under the Watchers and it's all for power. I just love that about her, rarely do you find villains who are just evil for the sake of evil anymore. They always have some ridiculous background to make us more sympathetic to their cause, and while I don't necessarily hate that, I do grow tired of it. Seriously, I really adore this champion, everyone who was involved in her development are just like the best people ever.
